"That's it!" cried Hatherley, in intense excitement. "There is the gravel-drive, and there are the
rose-bushes where I lay. That second window is the one that I jumped from."

"Well, at least," said Holmes, "you have had your revenge upon them. There can be no question that
it was your oil-lamp which, when it was crushed in the press, set fire to the wooden walls, though
no doubt they were too excited in the chase after you to observe it at the time. Now keep your eyes
open in this crowd for your friends of last night, though I very much fear that they are a good
hundred miles off by now."